==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Improvisation
<hw>Im*prov`i*sa"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>improvisation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or art of
composing and rendering music, poetry, and the like, extemporaneously;
<as>as, <ex>improvisation</ex> on the organ</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is improvised; an impromptu.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Improvisatize</ent>⟦br⟧
